411
00:46:47,296 --> 00:46:51,006
It’s been discontinued since a long time.

412
00:46:51,014 --> 00:47:01,334
I’m going to explain, talk about, the meaning of the time when they started doing that.

413
00:47:01,452 --> 00:47:06,212
They said that long ago, they didn’t used to do that.

414
00:47:06,600 --> 00:47:15,252
But when that child’s father had him sent to the bladders

415
00:47:15,263 --> 00:47:19,283
When they had sent him

416
00:47:19,295 --> 00:47:27,785
When he had stayed there for a year with the living beings, along with the seals, the bearded seals back then.

417
00:47:28,174 --> 00:47:34,224
Only when he had come back home the next year after his stay was complete

418
00:47:34,471 --> 00:47:38,821
That child had them start doing that.

419
00:47:40,197 --> 00:47:45,937
He had them start giving those seals water like that.

420
00:47:47,947 --> 00:47:52,927
After that time, they started doing that to [the seals].

421
00:47:52,931 --> 00:48:01,301
When he was a child, he had gone over there where the living [seals] go and stayed.

422
00:48:01,310 --> 00:48:05,630
And he only returned when a year had passed.

423
00:48:05,646 --> 00:48:11,356
Only when it was time for him to go did he return.

424
00:48:11,430 --> 00:48:14,390
He started that tradition.

425
00:48:14,480 --> 00:48:23,910
When they caught those seals, they wouldn’t throw their bladders away, but inflate them.

426
00:48:24,160 --> 00:48:30,400
They inflated the bladders of every seal down there, and kept them all summer.

427
00:48:30,411 --> 00:48:36,541
Then only when fall set did they pop them, stuff them under the ice, and had them drift away.

428
00:48:36,551 --> 00:48:42,161
They would do that with seals when they caught them.

429
00:48:42,172 --> 00:48:49,762
Its spirit might be there in its bladder. I think they say it’s in the bladder.

430
00:48:49,776 --> 00:48:55,356
They say they come the next year. They would say that.

431
00:48:55,368 --> 00:49:04,118
They say that those that were caught, that blatter returns to be caught again by the one who had caught it.

432
00:49:04,976 --> 00:49:11,176
That’s what they believed happened to them.

433
00:49:11,252 --> 00:49:18,882
They would send the bladders away, asking them to come again, when they held the Bladder Festival.

