460
00:51:48,613 --> 00:51:50,323
Okay, he...

461
00:51:50,335 --> 00:51:52,925
...[?] does it without doing it too hard.

462
00:51:53,475 --> 00:51:59,405
But he would do that with those that picked on him.

463
00:51:59,411 --> 00:52:00,281
I understand it.

464
00:52:00,839 --> 00:52:11,739
What he’s saying is that those people that were, or, those seals that he recognized that were good to him

465
00:52:11,750 --> 00:52:15,170
He made sure that he made a good, clean kill.

466
00:52:15,182 --> 00:52:19,172
You know, he really made sure that he did that.

467
00:52:19,267 --> 00:52:24,387
It seems like this was a really important ceremony to go through.

468
00:52:24,869 --> 00:52:30,890
Why did they stop that after Western contact?

469
00:52:34,801 --> 00:52:38,981
They stopped doing that when priests came.

470
00:52:39,124 --> 00:52:42,644
When these priests came

471
00:52:42,654 --> 00:52:52,334
With those legends, when these priests came, they relinquished that practice and stopped doing it.

472
00:52:52,341 --> 00:52:54,071
I see, like this?

473
00:52:54,154 --> 00:53:00,194
Which of these: out of shame, or did they tell you to stop?

474
00:53:00,957 --> 00:53:07,127
Though they weren’t told to stop, they stopped practicing that.

475
00:53:07,555 --> 00:53:15,055
The stopped practicing those practices they had with seals.

476
00:53:15,190 --> 00:53:18,860
Okay, I’ll do one, and I hear something different over there.

477
00:53:18,868 --> 00:53:25,198
But Kurt Bell says that after the missionaries came, they stopped on their own.

478
00:53:27,185 --> 00:53:29,675
May I speak?

479
00:53:29,686 --> 00:53:31,336
(Yes.) Okay.

480
00:53:31,339 --> 00:53:41,779
About the faces of bears, black bears or brown bears

481
00:53:41,791 --> 00:53:47,571
With the first catch, he evidently applies [saliva] from its mouth to his face.

482
00:53:49,296 --> 00:53:51,886
When I was a boy...

483
00:53:51,894 --> 00:53:54,864
(Who are you?) Edward Weiss.

484
00:53:56,885 --> 00:54:02,636
They said this to me, my grandfather:

485
00:54:04,062 --> 00:54:15,292
After shooting and killing a black bear, he’d then have me apply the salive from inside its mouth on my face and hands.

486
00:54:15,301 --> 00:54:18,791
Then he told me this:

487
00:54:19,306 --> 00:54:24,156
He said that when I grow up and start hunting

488
00:54:25,574 --> 00:54:36,464
He said that should a black bear or one of those brown bears get injured and takes me

489
00:54:36,473 --> 00:54:41,293
He said it’ll see my face covered in its saliva.

490
00:54:41,302 --> 00:54:45,292
He said that that [bear] won’t breathe on me.

491
00:54:45,303 --> 00:54:55,663
Black bears’ breath and saliva are very strong for people.

492
00:54:55,668 --> 00:55:00,508
That’s why they can kill by breathing on them, making their faces swell.

493
00:55:00,513 --> 00:55:02,823
He said it won’t do that to me.

494
00:55:02,831 --> 00:55:06,101
Then afterwards

495
00:55:06,927 --> 00:55:12,117
When I was some age, when I was 25

496
00:55:12,636 --> 00:55:16,486
I missed my gunshot, and a black bear took me.

497
00:55:16,495 --> 00:55:23,285
It took my gun like this, but it didn’t breath on my face.

498
00:55:23,294 --> 00:55:26,894
Instead, it looked away from me as it breathed.

499
00:55:26,906 --> 00:55:31,186
That’s what he instructed.

500
00:55:31,196 --> 00:55:36,186
Even now, at least in our village upriver.

501
00:55:36,738 --> 00:55:42,575
Okay, that’s Edward Weiss from Kuskokwim.

502
00:55:42,586 --> 00:55:44,366
He said when his grandfather...

503
00:55:46,935 --> 00:55:57,382
From her point of view of you older men

504
00:55:57,879 --> 00:56:04,629
She thought that you would respect, qigcikluki, animals you hunted.

505
00:56:04,638 --> 00:56:09,138
She asked if now, in your opinion

506
00:56:09,141 --> 00:56:17,611
Your descendants, are they doing that like you now?

507
00:56:17,626 --> 00:56:20,126
Or, she asked, are they not?

508
00:56:20,136 --> 00:56:27,496
Or if they’re not, she asked this: do you think animals will deplete?

509
00:56:30,903 --> 00:56:37,523
Now, I’m going to give some answer to her question.

510
00:56:37,990 --> 00:56:47,751
These seals, I don’t think of how the animals down from the ocean will be depleted.

511
00:56:48,793 --> 00:56:57,873
These instead, the birds, their chicks, and their eggs

512
00:56:58,011 --> 00:57:09,511
I admonish my descendants, my children, like this when their young hatch:

513
00:57:10,575 --> 00:57:14,680
Never to hunt.

514
00:57:15,068 --> 00:57:20,133
And never to [hunt] them when they’re chicks, when they’re small.

515
00:57:20,710 --> 00:57:32,420
Though their mothers bring forth a lot, when they have too few chicks, I admonish them against [hunting] them.

516
00:57:32,433 --> 00:57:42,023
Those children, my children, are probably like those chicks.

517
00:57:42,103 --> 00:57:45,753
They are the reason I admonish them.

518
00:57:45,768 --> 00:57:52,538
Though those birds’ eggs aren’t my children, when their chicks hatch.

519
00:57:53,246 --> 00:58:01,376
And when they’re bigger, if a person is chasing them to another place, I will admonish them

520
00:58:01,379 --> 00:58:09,089
Its mother, never to kill both it and its mother.

521
00:58:09,094 --> 00:58:14,194
The mothers, I tell them their chicks won’t have any caretakers.

522
00:58:14,321 --> 00:58:17,701
I say these seagulls don’t need anything else.

523
00:58:19,560 --> 00:58:27,880
I said their chicks would be pitiful without any mothers to take care of them.

524
00:58:28,337 --> 00:58:31,177
That’s why I admonish them.

525
00:58:34,077 --> 00:58:38,977
Well, he says that for him

526
00:58:38,984 --> 00:58:45,404
He doesn’t think that there’s not much danger to the seals right now.

527
00:58:45,412 --> 00:58:50,762
But he tells his children about the birds.

528
00:58:50,772 --> 00:58:57,972
That when birds have, you know, when the eggs are hatching

529
00:58:57,983 --> 00:59:03,423
And the mother, father birds have to take care of them...

530
00:59:04,539 --> 00:59:07,919
And it’s no different.

531
00:59:07,935 --> 00:59:18,325
We would hunt, then our mothers would honor our catch, be very thankful for it.

532
00:59:18,329 --> 00:59:25,849
Then now, we who’ve become fathers, that mother also know them since she has sons

533
00:59:25,852 --> 00:59:30,892
When her son catches a ptarmigan, she is very thankful and welcomes it.

534
00:59:30,901 --> 00:59:33,891
She doesn’t think it’s too little.

535
00:59:33,901 --> 00:59:39,301
She is thankful for and honors everything he catches.

536
00:59:39,311 --> 00:59:47,461
She doesn’t leave them strewn, or where people have trod since they’re are our ancient admonishments.

537
00:59:48,351 --> 00:59:51,071
He’s... these days...

538
00:59:51,081 --> 00:59:55,171
[S]he will was their face. I don’t know that.

539
00:59:55,180 --> 01:00:03,340
You see, we mothers who are younger than you have no instructors.

540
01:00:03,466 --> 01:00:14,166
Would it be good if you here had them speak on KYUK News

541
01:00:14,172 --> 01:00:20,342
Or, give them time to instruct us?

542
01:00:20,350 --> 01:00:24,480
We have many children trying to provide for themselves. We don’t know.

543
01:00:24,497 --> 01:00:27,647
I also leave my children in ignorance.

544
01:00:27,657 --> 01:00:32,147
It’s because I don’t hear of them since it’s been a long time since I’ve lost my mother.

545
01:00:32,155 --> 01:00:36,735
I like when these older people speak.

546
01:00:36,744 --> 01:00:42,134
They’re true. They still are now, but they’re disappearing.

547
01:00:42,148 --> 01:00:46,888
Western teachings that have appeared are eclipsing them.

548
01:00:47,046 --> 01:00:51,566
It would be good of the Caucasians among us gave us time.

549
01:00:51,578 --> 01:01:02,568
If an elder speaks on KYUK radio or on the news to teach our children, that will help us.

550
01:01:04,132 --> 01:01:09,882
We would be thankful if they gave them time.

551
01:01:09,893 --> 01:01:12,683
There’s much to learn.

552
01:01:13,469 --> 01:01:16,069
Thank you, Eliza.

553
01:01:16,483 --> 01:01:23,943
They instruct us when we’re going to hunt black bears...

554
01:01:28,579 --> 01:01:34,159
...that we should get a wooden staff.

555
01:01:35,483 --> 01:01:38,363
They said that that staff

556
01:01:38,370 --> 01:01:46,192
You know how a staff is useful in the fall for thin ice or for dangerous areas.

557
01:01:46,208 --> 01:01:52,458
That is a traditional instruction up north

558
01:01:52,466 --> 01:02:00,576
If we go to hunt a black bear in the mountains or travel anywhere, to always keep that staff on hand.

559
01:02:01,895 --> 01:02:09,881
Then when we travel for long enough, a black bear will attack us.

560
01:02:11,439 --> 01:02:19,609
They said that these black bears are like people. They grab like this like our hands.

561
01:02:20,307 --> 01:02:28,667
They said that before it takes our gun, that we should give it a staff right away.

562
01:02:28,673 --> 01:02:31,953
They said that that will save us.

563
01:02:31,964 --> 01:02:37,134
Give it to [the bear], it will take it, and we’ll shoot it.

564
01:02:45,130 --> 01:02:49,920
We had shamans. We evidently had shamans.

565
01:02:51,450 --> 01:02:56,850
We refer to those things back then as superstitions.

566
01:02:57,285 --> 01:03:02,525
They're superstitions. They're from shamans.

567
01:03:02,703 --> 01:03:07,753
Wait, wait, I don't understand that. "Piciruiq?"

568
01:03:07,934 --> 01:03:11,794
You know, it’s not true, but is from shamans.

569
01:03:11,800 --> 01:03:15,240
A shaman is of the devil, by what we call it.

570
01:03:15,249 --> 01:03:17,449
Those things

571
01:03:18,238 --> 01:03:26,288
When we got faith in God, many of those things, including medicine, have been given up.

572
01:03:26,290 --> 01:03:27,950
They’re given up now.

573
01:03:28,903 --> 01:03:36,583
Then in our village now down on the coast

574
01:03:38,284 --> 01:03:45,524
We don’t give up hunting for seals.

575
01:03:45,531 --> 01:03:59,032
Now, even if one is not young, ever year in the spring, when he catches the first seal

576
01:03:59,042 --> 01:04:02,262
Also having caught one the year before

577
01:04:02,272 --> 01:04:07,172
When the first man who goes spring seal hunting makes the first catch

578
01:04:08,565 --> 01:04:12,032
As we call it now, they distribute it.


